-Restricted Feeding' (14:10) to promote Migrating Motor Complex (MMC) function. Eliminate pro-inflammatory emulsifiers and processed sugars that fuel dysbiosis.\\\\n\\\\n## 2. Chronobiology & Sleep Architecture Optimization\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Restoration of HPA-Axis Balance and Circadian Glucose Regulation.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Circadian Alignment:** To address Insomnia and Afternoon Fatigue, prioritize morning sunlight exposure (15 mins) within 30 minutes of waking to anchor the cortisol awakening response (CAR). \\\\n*   **Sleep Hygiene for Glycemic Control:** Maintain a strict cool-temperature sleep environment. Discontinue blue-light exposure 120 minutes before bedtime to support endogenous melatonin production, which is critical for nocturnal glucose clearance and reducing Brain Fog.\\\\n*   **Night-time Fasting:** Ensure a minimum 3-hour gap between the last meal and sleep to prevent nocturnal insulin spikes and hepatic fat accumulation (ALT 42).\\\\n\\\\n## 3. Metabolic & Mitochondrial Conditioning\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Enhancement of Insulin Sensitivity and Non-Shivering Thermogenesis.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Zone 2 Aerobic Training:** 150 minutes per week of steady-state exercise (at a conversational pace) to improve mitochondrial density and metabolic flexibility, directly targeting the Metabolic Axis score of 80.\\\\n*   **Resistance Training (Hypertrophy-Focused):** 2 days/week to increase GLUT4 translocation and glucose disposal independent of insulin, crucial for reversing the pre-diabetic trajectory.\\\\n*   **Post-Prandial Thermogenesis:** A 10-minute 'Glucose Walk' immediately following the largest meal to blunt post-prandial glucose excursions.\\\\n\\\\n## 4. Neuromodulation & Stress Resilience\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Vagal Tone Enhancement and TNF-alpha Downregulation.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Vagus Nerve Stimulation (VNS) Exercises:** Implement diaphragmatic breathing or 'Box Breathing' (4-4-4-4) twice daily to transition the nervous system from Sympathetic dominance to Parasympathetic recovery, addressing the 'High Stress' occupation profile.\\\\n*   **Cognitive Load Management:** To combat Brain Fog, utilize 'Deep Work' blocks with 5-minute cognitive breaks to prevent prefrontal cortex exhaustion.\\\\n\\\\n## 5. Environmental & Targeted Supplementation Support\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Addressing Micronutrient Deficiencies and Toxic Load.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Vitamin D Repletion:** Targeted supplementation to raise Vitamin D from 22 ng/mL to an optimal range of 40-60 ng/mL for immune modulation and inflammatory control.\\\\n*   **Hormetic Stress:** Consideration of Sauna therapy (15 mins, 3x/week) to induce Heat Shock Proteins (HSPs) which assist in protein folding and cellular repair, further reducing systemic inflammation.\\\"}\",\"metadata\":{\"thoughtSignature\":\"\"}}]},\"finishReason\":\"stop\",\"custom\":{}}],\"custom\":{\"candidates\":[{\"content\":{\"parts\":[{\"text\":\"{\\\"chapter_title\\\":\\\"Chapter 18: Lifestyle Prescription - Systems Biology Integration\\\",\\\"patient_summary\\\":\\\"คุณจารุณี (Age 52) presents with Multi-Systemic Dysregulation characterized by Metabolic Syndrome (HbA1c 6.8), Systemic Inflammation (hs-CRP 4.5), and Gut Dysbiosis with Pathogenic Presence (Blastocystis hominis). The genomic landscape (MTHFR Heterozygous, TNF-alpha High Risk) necessitates a precision lifestyle intervention to modulate gene expression and restore homeostasis.\\\",\\\"lifestyle_prescription_content\\\":\\\"# Chapter 18: Lifestyle Prescription - Precision Systems Biology Approach\\\\n\\\\n## 1. Nutritional Pharmacology & Epigenetic Modulation\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Mitigate Insulin Resistance and Support Methylation Pathways.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Low-Glycemic Anti-Inflammatory Protocol:** Given the HbA1c of 6.8 and elevated TNF-alpha expression, a strict Mediterranean-Ketogenic hybrid is indicated. Focus on high-fiber phytonutrients to modulate the Firmicutes/Bacteroidetes ratio and reduce systemic inflammation (hs-CRP).\\\\n*   **Methylation Support (MTHFR Heterozygous/Homocysteine 15.2):** Increase intake of natural folates (dark leafy greens) and avoid synthetic folic acid. Limit methionine-rich animal proteins to moderate levels while ensuring adequate B12/B6 co-factors to drive the transsulfuration and remethylation pathways, reducing cardiovascular risk.\\\\n*   **Gut Hygiene & Biofilm Disruption:** To address *Blastocystis hominis* and low diversity, implement a 'Time-Restricted Feeding' (14:10) to promote Migrating Motor Complex (MMC) function. Eliminate pro-inflammatory emulsifiers and processed sugars that fuel dysbiosis.\\\\n\\\\n## 2. Chronobiology & Sleep Architecture Optimization\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Restoration of HPA-Axis Balance and Circadian Glucose Regulation.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Circadian Alignment:** To address Insomnia and Afternoon Fatigue, prioritize morning sunlight exposure (15 mins) within 30 minutes of waking to anchor the cortisol awakening response (CAR). \\\\n*   **Sleep Hygiene for Glycemic Control:** Maintain a strict cool-temperature sleep environment. Discontinue blue-light exposure 120 minutes before bedtime to support endogenous melatonin production, which is critical for nocturnal glucose clearance and reducing Brain Fog.\\\\n*   **Night-time Fasting:** Ensure a minimum 3-hour gap between the last meal and sleep to prevent nocturnal insulin spikes and hepatic fat accumulation (ALT 42).\\\\n\\\\n## 3. Metabolic & Mitochondrial Conditioning\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Enhancement of Insulin Sensitivity and Non-Shivering Thermogenesis.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Zone 2 Aerobic Training:** 150 minutes per week of steady-state exercise (at a conversational pace) to improve mitochondrial density and metabolic flexibility, directly targeting the Metabolic Axis score of 80.\\\\n*   **Resistance Training (Hypertrophy-Focused):** 2 days/week to increase GLUT4 translocation and glucose disposal independent of insulin, crucial for reversing the pre-diabetic trajectory.\\\\n*   **Post-Prandial Thermogenesis:** A 10-minute 'Glucose Walk' immediately following the largest meal to blunt post-prandial glucose excursions.\\\\n\\\\n## 4. Neuromodulation & Stress Resilience\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Vagal Tone Enhancement and TNF-alpha Downregulation.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Vagus Nerve Stimulation (VNS) Exercises:** Implement diaphragmatic breathing or 'Box Breathing' (4-4-4-4) twice daily to transition the nervous system from Sympathetic dominance to Parasympathetic recovery, addressing the 'High Stress' occupation profile.\\\\n*   **Cognitive Load Management:** To combat Brain Fog, utilize 'Deep Work' blocks with 5-minute cognitive breaks to prevent prefrontal cortex exhaustion.\\\\n\\\\n## 5. Environmental & Targeted Supplementation Support\\\\n**Primary Goal:** Addressing Micronutrient Deficiencies and Toxic Load.\\\\n\\\\n*   **Vitamin D Repletion:** Targeted supplementation to raise Vitamin D from 22 ng/mL to an optimal range of 40-60 ng/mL for immune modulation and inflammatory control.\\\\n*   **Hormetic Stress:** Consideration of Sauna therapy (15 mins, 3x/week) to induce Heat Shock Proteins (HSPs) which assist in protein folding and cellular repair, further reducing systemic inflammation.\\\"}\",\"thoughtSignature\":\"\"}],\"role\":\"model\"},\"finishReason\":\"STOP\",\"index\":0}],\"usageMetadata\":{\"promptTokenCount\":593,\"candidatesTokenCount\":949,\"totalTokenCount\":2326,\"promptTokensDetails\":[{\"modality\":\"TEXT\",\"tokenCount\":593}],\"thoughtsTokenCount\":784,\"serviceTier\":\"standard\"},\"modelVersion\":\"gemini-3-flash-preview\",\"responseId\":\"9DMEauLuGMXnjuMP9pXFsAE\"},\"usage\":{\"inputCharacters\":1632,\"inputImages\":0,\"inputVideos\":0,\"inputAudioFiles\":0,\"outputCharacters\":4161,\"outputImages\":0,\"outputVideos\":0,\"outputAudioFiles\":0,\"inputTokens\":593,\"outputTokens\":949,\"thoughtsTokens\":784,\"totalTokens\":2326},\"latencyMs\":11422.780161000002}","genkit:state":"success"},"displayName":"googleai/gemini-flash-latest","links"